co.cask.cdap.api.workflow

Interface WorkflowContext

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DatasetContext, PluginContext, RuntimeContext, ServiceDiscoverer

    public interface WorkflowContext
extends RuntimeContext, ServiceDiscoverer, DatasetContext, PluginContext
    Represents the runtime context of a Workflow. This context is also available to WorkflowAction.

      • getNodeStates

        @Beta
Map<String,WorkflowNodeState> getNodeStates()
        Return an immutable Map of node ids to WorkflowNodeState. This can be used from AbstractWorkflow.destroy() method to determine the status of all nodes executed by the Workflow in the current run.

      • isSuccessful

        @Beta
boolean isSuccessful()
        Return true if the execution was successful, false otherwise. This method can be used from AbstractWorkflow.destroy() to determine the status of the Workflow. It can also be used from WorkflowAction.destroy() method to determine the status of the WorkflowAction. If it is called before the execution is completed, false is returned.
